      <div id="longest" about="[flabel:longest]" typeof="owl:DatatypeProperty">
        <h4 property="rdfs:label">longest</h4>
        <p property="rdfs:comment">When this flag is set to true, and the sorting is lexical, longer strings, rather than shorter, come first.</p>
        <blockquote class="note">
          <p property="skos:note">In a conventional lexical sort, two strings which start out identical but one is longer, the longer string will be placed after the shorter one. This flag signals the opposite behaviour.</p>
        </blockquote>
        <dl>
          <dt>Domain:</dt>
          <dd><a rel="external rdfs:domain" href="http://www.w3.org/2004/09/fresnel#PropertyDescription">fresnel:PropertyDescription</a></dd>
          <dt>Range:</dt>
          <dd><a rel="external rdfs:range" href="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">xsd:boolean</a></dd>
